uminates the political meanings that the images of ethnic woman and family have taken on in popular discourse.A provocative study that sets the reflections of a broad range of Italian-Americans in the context of their varied life histories, this book provides an informed commentary on family, class, culture, and gender in American life.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aItalian American familieszCaliforniazSan Francisco Bay Area. 0aItalian AmericanszCaliforniazSan Francisco Bay AreaxEthnic identity. 0aKinshipzCaliforniazSan Francisco Bay Area. 4aAnthropology. 4aDiscrimination & Race Relations. 4aU.S. History.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Archive Pre-2000z978311053617140uhttps://doi.org/10.7591/978150172125040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501721250423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501721250/original  a978-3-11-053617-1  Cornell University Press Archive Pre-2000b2000  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_PPALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles